name: CKError.Code
desc: The error codes that CloudKit returns.

items.name: case accountTemporarilyUnavailable
items.desc: An error that occurs when the user’s iCloud account is temporarily unavailable.

items.name: case alreadyShared
items.desc: An error that occurs when CloudKit attempts to share a record with an existing share.

items.name: case assetFileModified
items.desc: An error that occurs when the system modifies an asset while saving it.

items.name: case assetFileNotFound
items.desc: An error that occurs when the system can’t find the specified asset.

items.name: case assetNotAvailable
items.desc: An error that occurs when the system can’t access the specified asset.

items.name: case badContainer
items.desc: An error that occurs when you use an unknown or unauthorized container.

items.name: case badDatabase
items.desc: An error that occurs when the operation can’t complete for the specified database.

items.name: case batchRequestFailed
items.desc: An error that occurs when the system rejects the entire batch of changes.

items.name: case changeTokenExpired
items.desc: An error that occurs when the change token expires.

items.name: case constraintViolation
items.desc: An error that occurs when the server rejects the request because of a unique constraint violation.

items.name: case incompatibleVersion
items.desc: An error that occurs when the current app version is older than the oldest allowed version.

items.name: case internalError
items.desc: A nonrecoverable error that CloudKit encounters.

items.name: case invalidArguments
items.desc: An error that occurs when the request contains invalid information.

items.name: case limitExceeded
items.desc: An error that occurs when a request’s size exceeds the limit.

items.name: case managedAccountRestricted
items.desc: An error that occurs when CloudKit rejects a request due to a managed-account restriction.

items.name: case missingEntitlement
items.desc: An error that occurs when the app is missing a required entitlement.

items.name: case networkFailure
items.desc: An error that occurs when a network is available, but CloudKit is inaccessible.

items.name: case networkUnavailable
items.desc: An error that occurs when the network is unavailable.

items.name: case notAuthenticated
items.desc: An error that occurs when the user is unauthenticated.

items.name: case operationCancelled
items.desc: An error that occurs when an operation cancels.

items.name: case partialFailure
items.desc: An error that occurs when an operation completes with partial failures.

items.name: case participantMayNeedVerification
items.desc: An error that occurs when the user isn’t a participant of the share.

items.name: case permissionFailure
items.desc: An error that occurs when the user doesn’t have permission to save or fetch data.

items.name: case quotaExceeded
items.desc: An error that occurs when saving a record exceeds the user’s storage quota.

items.name: case referenceViolation
items.desc: An error that occurs when CloudKit can’t find the target of a reference.

items.name: case requestRateLimited
items.desc: An error that occurs when CloudKit rate-limits requests.

items.name: case serverRecordChanged
items.desc: An error that occurs when CloudKit rejects a record because the server’s version is different.

items.name: case serverRejectedRequest
items.desc: An error that occurs when CloudKit rejects the request.

items.name: case serverResponseLost
items.desc: An error that occurs when CloudKit is unable to maintain the network connection and provide a response.

items.name: case serviceUnavailable
items.desc: An error that occurs when CloudKit is unavailable.

items.name: case tooManyParticipants
items.desc: An error that occurs when a share has too many participants.

items.name: case unknownItem
items.desc: An error that occurs when the specified record doesn’t exist.

items.name: case userDeletedZone
items.desc: An error that occurs when the user deletes a record zone using the Settings app.

items.name: case zoneBusy
items.desc: An error that occurs when the server is too busy to handle the record zone operation.

items.name: case zoneNotFound
items.desc: An error that occurs when the specified record zone doesn’t exist.
